<TITLE> IOSA enrols Biman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31 (bdnews24.com)  Biman Bangladesh Airlines has appeared on the IATA Operational Safety Audit register, which is now a prerequisite for retaining IATA membership, the flag carrier has said. The safety audit covers eight operational areas  organisation, engineering/maintenance, flight operations, ground service, airport service, flight service, cargo, security and also training, a Biman press release said on Wednesday. Biman faced the IOSA audit in Dec. 2007, was cleared by the international auditors and placed on the IOSA registry in Dec. 2008. The national flag carrier had to conform to more than 800 IATA safety standards to meet the audit, the statement said. The press statement, signed by Biman's director planning, Nafees Ahmed Imtiazuddin, said, conformity with the standards makes Biman 'a truly safe airline'. "Insurance premium can get lower and it also puts Biman in a far better position in the matter of insurance claims settlement," the statement said. Biman has joined 271 international airlines on the IOSA registry. bd
